Nike Popoola The Chairman, Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria, Mowe and District Society, Nyakno Ololade, has expressed the commitment to enhance the technical competence of members and reposition the institute. She said this in a statement titled ‘ICAN president lays foundation for ICAN Mowe house, inaugurates new district’s executives’. “ICAN Mowe and District Society is set for a new frontier in upholding the tenets of the institute, enhancing the technical competence and entrepreneurial developments of members, as well as innovatively repositioning the institute for greater visibility and national relevance,” she said. The statement said this was some of the highlights of her acceptance speech as the fourth chairman of the district, during her investiture recently. According to her, the future of the profession and the country at large lies in the hands of the youths who are strategically prepared, nurtured and positioned to take over the mantle of leadership of the country. The new chairman said she planned to achieve this through the establishment of future accountants club across the secondary schools with her jurisdiction to benefit from various leadership and strategic mentoring programme. Oluokun, at the occasion, inaugurated the new executive members of the district after taking the oath of office. The statement said before her investiture, Oluokun led a delegation of the ICAN presidency to the official foundation laying of ICAN Mowe House site. Copyright PUNCH.
